---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Other Paid Social Platforms"
  description="Paid social management on LinkedIn and Pinterest, plus other emerging platforms, evaluated on merit for your audience."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Paid Social / Other Platforms"
    title="Beyond Facebook and Instagram"
    description="Not every audience lives on Meta. Where LinkedIn, Pinterest or another platform genuinely fits your audience, we'll say so — and manage it properly."
  />

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 space-y-16">
    <div class="grid gap-10 sm:grid-cols-2 sm:items-start">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-slate">LinkedIn</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-brand-slate-light">
          The default choice for B2B lead generation and account-based targeting. We use native lead gen forms to
          cut friction, and target by job title, seniority and named account lists rather than broad industry
          categories.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-slate">Pinterest</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-brand-slate-light">
          High-intent discovery advertising, particularly strong for retail and lifestyle brands. Shopping
          campaigns built from your product feed reach people who are actively planning a purchase, and Pins keep
          driving traffic well beyond the campaign flight.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 text-brand-slate-light">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-slate">Weighing up a newer platform?</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-sm">
        TikTok, Snapchat, Reddit and others come up regularly in planning conversations. We'll assess any of them
        against your audience and budget honestly — recommending a test only where the fit is genuine, not because
        it's the newest option on the table.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBanner />
</BaseLayout>
